{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014g1i13h7DtHJHc84eeZ62f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem! The ConfigMap for `elasticsearch.yml` is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. This is the bootstrap setting required for the first time a cluster forms. Without it, the nodes don't know which nodes can bootstrap the cluster.\n\nIn Elasticsearch 7.x, when starting a new cluster, you need:\n1. `cluster.initial_master_nodes` - lists which nodes are eligible to be the initial master for the bootstrap\n\nWithout `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, the nodes can't bootstrap the cluster. This is the \"master not discovered yet\" error.\nThe fix is to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap to allow the cluster to form initially, then remove it afterward since it's only needed for bootstrap and can cause issues with re-election once the cluster is established. Looking at the current elasticsearch.yml configuration, I can see it's missing this critical setting along with the discovery configuration. for the cluster to form, then strip out the bootstrap setting and do another rolling restart to finalize the configuration. Let me review the logs to verify this is actually what's blocking cluster formation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":647,"cache_read_input_tokens":31781,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":647},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a57abbbe-5f0f-4c71-885d-cc856f5e9fc9","uuid":"c87c5f8a-ff84-4de7-8a7e-1ebfb84d8384","request_id":"req_011Ccer3A9XrLa5SbtXUrYVe"}
