{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Ttw1WTNLeEtfH8cgpRV7B9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The exit code 1 means `grep -c` found 0 occurrences — the bootstrap setting is absent. Everything is clean.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of what was done and why:**\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-config` ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. In Elasticsearch 7.x, this is a required bootstrap-only setting for a brand-new cluster — without it, nodes discover each other but cannot elect a master (hence \"master not discovered yet\").\n\n**Fix in 3 steps:**\n\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]`** to the ConfigMap and deleted all 3 pods simultaneously (safe since the cluster hadn't formed yet; `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` means they restart together and immediately hold a bootstrap election).\n\n2. **Cluster formed** — green status, 3 nodes, master elected (`es-cluster-2`).\n\n3. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** from the ConfigMap, then did `kubectl rollout restart statefulset/es-cluster` for a rolling restart. `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is a bootstrap-only setting: leaving it in place after cluster formation is dangerous because it can trigger an illegitimate second bootstrap if ever applied to a fresh node set. The cluster remembers its formation in the persistent data directory — `discovery.seed_hosts` handles future restarts from here on.\n\n**Final state:**\n- Cluster status: **green**, 3 nodes, 1 master elected\n- Rolling restart completed with cluster staying healthy throughout\n- ConfigMap contains only safe, restart-stable settings"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":275,"cache_read_input_tokens":42061,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":275},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a57abbbe-5f0f-4c71-885d-cc856f5e9fc9","uuid":"4bd12a5a-aeef-4dee-9573-ab46bccce41e","request_id":"req_011Cces5SGZkdnYannN7kQZj"}
